{ Annotated by IM Nitish Belurkar https://lichess.org/@/kingnb }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 { Petroff...known for its calm tendencies and used as a reliable shield! } 3. d4 Nxe4 4. dxe5 Bc5 5. Qd5 { The intentions here are clear, Harikrishna is out for blood } 5... Bxf2+ (5... Nxf2 6. Qxc5 Nxh1 7. Bg5 $18) 6. Ke2 f5 7. Nc3 c6 8. Nxe4! { The idea Hari kept in his pocket for 9 years, before he could finally reveal it } 8... cxd5 9. Nd6+ Kf8 10. Kxf2 Nc6 11. Be3 d4 12. Bf4 Qb6 13. Bd3 { White now has the upper hand } 13... Ne7 14. Bd2 Nd5 15. Bxf5 Ne3 (15... d3+ 16. Kg3 $18 { Whites king is safe in the open, black king at home is in danger }) 16. Bd3 Ke7 17. Rhe1 Rf8 18. Rxe3!! { Sacrifice the roooook! Going for the king! } 18... dxe3+ 19. Bxe3 Rxf3+ (19... Qxb2 20. Bg5+ Ke6 (20... Rf6 21. Re1 $18 { Carnage }) 21. Bc4#) 20. Kxf3! Qxb2 21. Bg5+ Ke6 22. Re1 b5 23. Bf5+ Kd5 24. Be4+ Ke6 25. Bxa8 Qc3+ 26. Re3 Qxc2 27. Be4 Qd1+ 28. Kg3 Qh5 29. h4 { A perfect game by Harikrishna! Summoning his inner Tal! } 1-0


