{ Annotated by IM Nitish Belurkar https://lichess.org/@/kingnb }
1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. c3 d6 { Kacper chooses a relatively rare line in the Italian with the Black pieces } (4... Nf6 { The most mainstream response }) 5. d4 { Wei Yi reacts with a generic break in the center } 5... exd4 6. cxd4 Bb6 7. Nc3 { Wei Yi decides to delay the decision to castle } (7. O-O Bg4 { Heads into a tricky line } 8. Bb5 (8. d5 Bxf3 9. Qxf3 (9. gxf3 Ne5 10. Bb5+ c6 11. Be2 cxd5 12. f4 Nd7 $13) 9... Ne5 10. Qe2 Qh4 $15) 8... a6 9. Ba4 Ba7 10. d5 b5 11. dxc6 bxa4 $14) 7... Nf6 (7... Bg4 { Is lesser effective now } 8. Bb5 a6 (8... Bd7 { A sad retreat } 9. Be3 $16) 9. Ba4 Ba7 10. d5 b5 11. Nxb5 axb5 12. Bxb5 $18) 8. Be3 Nxe4?! { Black rushes too soon, with the king still in the center } (8... O-O 9. Bb3 { Getting away from the Nxe4 threat } 9... Bg4 10. Qd3 Nb4 11. Qc4 c5 12. O-O { Black is fine }) 9. Nxe4 d5 10. Bb3 dxe4 11. Ng5 { Black king is stuck in the center, as the White pieces target beside it } 11... Be6 (11... O-O? { Risks the king safety even more } 12. Qh5 h6 13. Nxf7 $18) (11... Qe7 12. Bxf7+ Kf8 13. Bb3 Nxd4 14. Bxd4 Qxg5 15. h4 Qe7 16. Rc1 $16 { White has the safer king and the active pieces }) 12. Nxe6 { Wei Yi loses the advantage, but holds the 2 strong bishops } (12. Bxe6 { The right capture } 12... fxe6 13. Nxe6 Qd5 14. Qg4 g6 15. O-O $18) 12... fxe6 13. O-O Bxd4? { Kacper ignores the king safety again } (13... Qf6 { Would help Black keep balance } 14. Qg4 Qf5 15. Bxe6 Qxg4 16. Bxg4 Nxd4) 14. Qh5+ g6 15. Qg4? { Not the right square for the queen } (15. Qb5! { Moves across the board hitting the b7 pawn } 15... O-O 16. Qxb7 Bxe3 17. fxe3 Qd6 18. Rfd1 Qc5 19. Bxe6+ Kh8 20. Qxc7 Qxe3+ 21. Kh1 Qb6 22. Qxb6 axb6 23. Bd5 Rac8 24. Bxe4 $16 { White has an extra pawn heading to the endgame }) 15... Qf6?? (15... Bxe3 { The right way to go about and ensure the Black king is safe } 16. fxe3 (16. Qxe6+ Qe7) 16... Qe7 17. Rad1 Rd8 18. Bxe6 Rxd1 19. Rxd1 Ne5 20. Qh3 Kf8 21. Qh6+ Ke8) 16. Bxe6 { The bishop on e6 makes sure the Black king does not reach safety now } 16... Ne5 (16... Bxe3 17. fxe3 Qe5 18. Rad1 $18 { The Black king gets sandwiched at home }) 17. Qxe4 Bxe3 (17... Qxe6 18. Bxd4 $18) 18. Bf7+!! { A brilliant intermezzo by Wei Yi, missed by Kacper Piorun, the 6 time Puzzle solving champion himself } 18... Kxf7 (18... Qxf7 19. Qxe5+ Qe7 20. Qxh8+ $18) 19. fxe3 { White now gets the queen! } 19... Rhe8 20. Qxb7 { The queen isn't running anywhere } 20... Qxf1+ 21. Rxf1+ Kg8 22. Qxc7 a5 23. a4 Rad8 24. Qxa5 Nc4 25. Qc3 Nd2 26. Rd1 { A brilliant start to the event for Wei Yi, with a game to showcase his strength in calculation and class! } 1-0


