{ Annotated by IM Nitish Belurkar https://lichess.org/@/kingnb }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 cxd4 { Vokhidov opts for the Semi-Tarrasch, known for its drawing tendencies } 6. Qa4+ Bd7 7. Qxd4 exd5 8. Nxd5 Qa5+ 9. Nc3 Nc6 10. Qd1 Ne4 { Black is well prepared, Arjun had played the same line as White against Wei Yi, at the Norway chess } 11. Bd2 Nxd2 12. Nxd2 (12. Qxd2 O-O-O 13. Qc1 Bf5 14. a3 g5 $13 { Leads to a complex position with good compensation for the pawn for black }) 12... Bb4 13. Rc1 Bxc3 14. Rxc3 Qxa2 15. Nc4 Be6 16. e4 Rd8 17. Nd6+ Kf8 { Vokhidov heads the right way! } (17... Ke7? { The mistake Wei Yi had made at Norway chess } 18. Qc1! Rxd6 (18... Qa4 19. Nxb7 Rc8 (19... Qxe4+ 20. Be2 Qxg2 21. Bf3 $18) 20. Qg5+ { The reason why Ke7 is a mistake } 20... Kf8 21. Nc5 $18 Qa1+ 22. Qc1 Qxc1+ 23. Rxc1 $18) 19. Ra3 $18 { traps the Queen }) 18. Qd2 { Arjun, all ready to outprep his opponents prep } (18. Qc1 { Is the more usual way of playing } 18... Qa4 19. Nxb7 Qxe4+ 20. Qe3 Qxe3+ 21. fxe3) 18... Qa4 (18... Qa1+ 19. Rc1 Qa4 20. Bb5 Qd4) 19. f4!? { White heads on to roll on his pawns in the center, as black pieces remain uncoordinated } 19... Qb4 20. e5 f6? (20... g5! { Hits right in the center } 21. Bb5 Ne7! 22. fxg5 Ng6 23. Rd3 Qxd2+ 24. Rxd2 Nxe5) 21. Bd3 (21. Bb5! { Was the better choice } 21... Ne7 22. Bd3 $16) 21... fxe5 (21... Ke7 22. O-O Rhf8 $14 { Is a very computer way to play }) 22. fxe5 Nxe5 23. O-O+ Kg8 (23... Ke7 24. Nf5+ Bxf5 (24... Kd7 25. Bb5#) 25. Rc7+ $18 { Drops the Black queen }) 24. Bf5! Bf7 (24... Bb3 25. Qe3 Qxd6 26. Rxb3 $18) 25. Rc8! Qb6+ (25... Qxd2 { A queen sacrifice } 26. Rxd8+ Be8 27. Rxe8# { Gets the king }) (25... Qxd6 26. Qxd6 $18) 26. Rf2 (26. Kh1 { Would work as well } 26... g6 27. Rxd8+ Qxd8 28. Qd4 Nc6 (28... Qe7 29. Re1 Nc6 30. Rxe7 Nxd4 31. Nxf7 Nxf5 32. Rxb7 $18 { The rook on h8 is trapped }) 29. Qxh8+! Kxh8 30. Nxf7+ Kg7 31. Nxd8 $18 { A rook up! }) 26... Rxc8 27. Bxc8 h5 28. Nxf7 { The final blow! } 28... Nxf7 29. Qd5 Kh7 (29... Qc7 30. Be6 $18) 30. Qxf7 { 1-0 White wins. } 1-0


