{ Annotated by IM Nitish Belurkar https://lichess.org/@/kingnb }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 { The Nizmo, a top choice of many, was chosen by Anish, who has already qualified himself for the Candidates event, through the Grand Swiss } 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 Re8 6. Ne2 { A very subtle line chosen by Alexander Donchenko } 6... d5 7. O-O Bf8 8. e4!? { Breaking open the center quick! } 8... dxe4 9. Nxe4 Nxe4 10. Bxe4 Nd7 (10... e5!? { Black could opt to open up the game too! } 11. dxe5 Qxd1 12. Rxd1 Rxe5 13. Nc3 Re8 14. Bf4 { White enjoys better developed and more active pieces }) 11. Qc2 f5!? { A bold move from Anish, a committal move! } (11... Nf6 12. Bf3 e5 13. dxe5 Ng4! 14. Be4 g6 15. Bf4 Nxe5 { Black can soon release his pieces }) 12. Bf3 c6 13. g3 e5 { Anish picks the right time to push the pawn! } 14. Bg2 (14. Qxf5? exd4 { Opening the e5 square for the knight in order to attack the misplaced White queen } 15. Nxd4 (15. Bg5 Qb6 16. Rfd1 Ne5 17. Qe4 d3 $19) 15... Ne5 16. Qf4 Qxd4 17. Qxd4 Nxf3+ 18. Kg2 Nxd4 $19) 14... exd4?! { rushed too soon } (14... e4 { Would have been more ideal, keeping the center locked } 15. f3 exf3 16. Bxf3 Nf6 17. Bf4 Be6 18. Rad1 Qd7) 15. Nxd4 Ne5 16. Rd1 Qf6 17. c5! { White now is ready to mobilise his pieces to the right square, but first ensures, that the Black pieces are locked } 17... a5 18. b3 Qf7? { Anish finds it tough to make a choice with less space to play } (18... Nd7 { Hitting at the c5 pawn! } 19. Bb2 Qg6 20. Ba3 f4 { Essential for Black to get the queens off the board } 21. Qxg6 hxg6 22. Re1 (22. Rac1 fxg3 23. hxg3 Ne5) 22... Rxe1+ 23. Rxe1 fxg3 24. hxg3 Bxc5 { Begins a forced sequence of moves for Black } 25. Bxc5 Nxc5 26. Re8+ Kf7 27. Rh8 Ke7 28. Bh3 Nd7) 19. h3 h6 20. Re1! $14 { Donchenko now senses the need to freeze Black pieces even more } 20... Bd7 (20... Nd7 21. Ba3 $16 { Is now a better version for White }) 21. f4 Ng6 22. Be3 { In a position where White enjoys space, Alexander wants more pieces on the board } 22... Re7 23. Bf2 Rae8 { Anish Giri finally gets his final rook where it is wanted, but is late } 24. Rxe7 (24. Red1 { White should keep his pieces alive, and now Black has no life in his pieces } 24... Nh8 25. Rd2 g5 { Desperate ways to untangle the pieces } 26. Bf1 Qf6 27. Rad1 Nf7 28. Bd3 $18) 24... Nxe7 { The ugly knight on g6 heads out in search of a new life at d5 } 25. Re1 Nd5 26. Rxe8 Qxe8 27. Nxf5 $14 { White is now a pawn up, but Black pieces are finally able to breathe! } 27... Nb4 (27... Qg6?? { This pin backfires } 28. Bxd5+ cxd5 29. Ne7+ { Drops the Black queen } 29... Bxe7 30. Qxg6 $18) 28. Qb1 Qh5? { Not the right square } (28... Qe6 { The right way for Black to hit the knight, holding d6 square too } 29. Nh4 g5!? 30. fxg5 hxg5 31. Nf3 g4 32. hxg4 Qxg4 33. Ne5 Qf5 $14 { With good chances to hold for Black }) 29. Nd6 { The knight is again pressing the Black bishops } 29... Bxh3 30. Bxh3 Qxh3 31. Qg6 $18 { The greed to get back the lost pawn for Black does not end well, as the Black king suffers } 31... Qd7 32. f5? { The f5 square was supposed to be for the White knight } (32. Kh2 { Away from all threats } 32... Qe7 (32... Nd5 33. Nf5 Kh8 34. Bd4 $18) 33. Nf5 Qe2 34. Nxh6+ Kh8 35. Ng4 $18) 32... Nd5 33. Bd4 Qe7 $14 { Black has managed to stop the vicious f6 threat, and all of white pieces are now frozen } 34. Kf1 b5 35. a4 bxa4 36. bxa4 { The queen side is now fixed } 36... Qd7?? (36... Ne3+! { The only move for black to maintain balance } 37. Bxe3 (37. Kf2 Nc2 38. Bc3 Qe3+ 39. Kg2 Qxc3 40. Qe6+ Kh7 41. Qg6+ Kg8 42. Qe6+) 37... Qxe3 38. Qe6+ Qxe6 39. fxe6 g6) 37. f6 { White waited for this for 5 moves } 37... Nxf6 38. Bxf6 Qe6 (38... Qh3+ 39. Kg1 $18 { No more checks }) 39. Ne4 Qc4+ 40. Kg2 Qe2+ 41. Kh3 { The king on its way to run for safety } 41... Qf1+ 42. Kg4 Qd1+ 43. Kf5 Qd7+ 44. Kf4 { Finally a safe spot, close to the center of the board } 44... Qe6 (44... Qc7+ 45. Be5 $18 { Saves the bishop and the king }) 45. g4 Qc4 46. Bc3 Qf1+ 47. Ke5 { Alexander wins king of the hill too! A whole extra piece for White, Alexander knocks out Anish out in round 3 } 1-0


