{ Annotated by IM Nitish Belurkar https://lichess.org/@/kingnb }
1. d4 e6 2. c4 b6 3. e4 Bb7 4. Bd3 f5?! { A must win game with Black for Fedoseev, and he shows desperation early on } 5. exf5 (5. Nc3 { The simple Nc3, comes with its fair share of challenges } 5... Bb4 6. Ne2 fxe4 7. Bc2 Nf6 8. O-O O-O $13) 5... Bxg2 6. Qh5+ { Radoslow Wojtasek accepts the challenge! } 6... g6 7. fxg6 Bg7 (7... Nf6?? 8. g7+! Nxh5 9. gxh8=Q $18 { Replaces the lost queen and White is winning }) 8. gxh7+ { Blacks whole king side is set ablaze, but White has a rook that is stuck at home } 8... Kf8 9. Bg5 (9. hxg8=Q+? { Loses White all his advantage } 9... Kxg8 10. Qg4 Bxh1 11. Bg5 Qe8 12. h4 $13 { Complex equality }) 9... Nf6 10. Qh4 Bxh1 { Black is up a rook for just 2 pawns, but the Black king is not safe yet } 11. Ne2 Nc6 12. Nbc3? { Radoslaw makes his first big error of the game } (12. Nd2 { Essential to hold the f3 square to trap the h1 bishop in } 12... e5 13. f3 Qe7 (13... Nb4 14. Bf5 $18) 14. O-O-O Qf7 15. Rxh1 exd4 16. Rg1 $18 { White will soon rush in and destroy enemy camp }) (12. Nf4? { Is too soon } 12... e5! 13. Ng6+ Kf7 14. dxe5 Rxh7 15. Qg3 Nh5 16. Qg4 Bf6! 17. exf6 Nxf6 18. Qf4 Rh3 $13 { Very impractical play, that black would enjoy having for the game }) 12... e5! { Black takes action, hitting in the center } 13. O-O-O exd4 { The knight is now attacked, and black is opening the position chances for himself } 14. Rxh1? (14. Nxd4 Nxd4 15. Qxd4 { Would hold the position for white } 15... Ne4 16. Qxg7+ Kxg7 17. Bxd8 Nxc3 18. Rg1+ Kf7 19. bxc3 Rhxd8 20. Rxh1 Kg7 { The pawn on h7 is dangerous }) 14... dxc3 { Black will enjoy consolidating the pieces and to enjoy the material advantage } 15. Nf4 Ne5 16. Bc2? (16. Be4 { The right square for the bishop } 16... c6 17. Nh5 Rxh7 18. Bxh7 Nf3 19. Bxf6 Nxh4 20. Bxd8 cxb2+ 21. Kc2 Rxd8 22. Nxg7 Kxg7 23. Be4 { As the dust settles, both players find themselves in a drawn endgame }) 16... Kf7? (16... Nf3! { Looking to trade as many pieces as possible } 17. Ng6+ (17. Qg3 cxb2+ 18. Kd1 (18. Kb1 Nd2+ 19. Kxb2 Nfe4+ 20. Kc1 Nxg3 21. Bxd8 Nxh1 $19) 18... Nxg5 19. Ng6+ Ke8 20. Qxg5 Rxh7 21. Re1+ Kf7 $19 { Black enjoys the material advantage }) 17... Ke8 (17... Kf7 { Allows a check on h8 } 18. Nxh8+ Bxh8 19. Qh6 Nxg5 20. Bg6+ Ke7 21. Qxg5 $15) 18. Qf4 Nxg5 19. Qxg5 Rxh7 $19 { Black finds himself with an extra rook }) 17. Nh5! { White finds the move, disrupting Black's major defensive pieces } 17... Nf3 { A move too late } (17... Rxh7 18. Bxh7 cxb2+ 19. Kb1 Qh8 20. Nxf6 Bxf6 21. Qh5+ Ke6 22. h4 $18 { Black has now regained the rook and has 2 pawns that will run outside }) 18. Qf4 Nxg5 19. Qxg5 { The king is stuck } 19... Qf8 (19... Nxh5 20. Qxh5+ Kf8 21. Qf3+ Qf6 (21... Bf6 22. Rd1 { The extra Black rook on h8 is held by a single White pawn } 22... cxb2+ 23. Kb1 d6 24. Re1 $18) 22. Qxa8+ $18) 20. Bg6+ { Black resigned seeing what was to come. The desperation from Fedoseev had backfired, as Radoslaw Wojtasek made it through! } 1-0


